<br>
With my solo mage (non-twink but the 5th I've started) I went to Erud's crossing at lvl 8 and left at around 15-16).<br>
<br>
At lvl 8 any adds are death, at lvl 15 you start to wish there was 1 more spawn...<br>
<br>
As for the layout, there are 4 &quot;corners&quot; of the island.  going clockwise these are 1) docks  2) wisp spawn 3) quest ogre, and 4) cat fishing.<br>
<br>
It is possible to &quot;share&quot; the island, but most of the time I didn't have to on Rathe.  It doesn't seem many low levellers come here anymore.<br>
<br>
If the island is fully spawned, there are 5 wisps up, often I've found 1 or 2 between docks and spawn, 1 02 2 on hill near cat fisher (or in center volcano area) and 1 near the ogre.<br>
<br>
All 5 will respawn at (or very near) the same spot (corner counter-clockwise of docks) and they initially travel clockwise past ogre to a hill with 2 glowing rocks.  From here I haven't tracked their progress, I usually camp on their path from spawn to the ogre.<br>
<br>
Now for important stuff...<br>
No, the ogre has never been aggro to me.  I've rarely found one off in the water,  don't swim looking for them (some very serious sharks near island that can see invis).<br>
<br>
I usually used a water elemental at this level, renew summoned is often very efficient in mana usage per fight (nuke once and heal pet til you win...).  Of course if you know what you are doing any of the pets can be effective (the fire's DS may be more suitable for my tactics here...)<br>
<br>
The respawn time if controlling all 5 is reasonable with just enough downtime to regain mana (barely).<br>
<br>
As for the other spawns on the island.  1) katta will assist beetles under attack 2) The poison fo the spiders and snakes can be significant (on you, pet can ususally handle).  3) the vampire bat with a pet is an undercon (without pets they are reasonably easy).  4) Killing spiders, snakes, etc may spawn some tougher critters, notable madmen and elementals.  be careful if others are on island killing indiscriminately.  The only aggro I've gotten on the island was from madmen, elementals, and zombie sailors.  when I was alone AFK was a pretty safe place to be.<br>
<br>
